results.snippet: FARMINGDALE, L. I., Jan. 2 -- The technical jargon that has grown out of recent probes into outer space has prompted the Republic Aviation Corporation to publish what it describes as a layman's guide to "the lexicographic labyrinth" of space science.

headline.main: 110 Selected as Potential Pilots For Nation's First Space Flight; Rigid Tests Will Narrow List to One for Hazardous Venture Into Orbit 110 ARE SELECTED FOR SPACE FLIGHT

results.snippet: The new Federal space agency has selected 110 candidates for possible assignment as the test pilot of the nation's first space capsule. The agency expects to narrow the list to twelve volunteers by late March.
